1
00:00:03,510 --> 00:00:04,750
- Okay?
- Yes, sir.

2
00:00:04,820 --> 00:00:05,820
Serim!

3
00:00:08,020 --> 00:00:09,290
(Go Woo-young)

4
00:00:40,850 --> 00:00:42,290
Are you going home now?

5
00:00:43,590 --> 00:00:44,590
Yes.

6
00:00:48,460 --> 00:00:50,090
Wasn't Si-woo amazing today?

7
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:51,900
He's been better.

8
00:00:54,170 --> 00:00:55,170
I see.

9
00:00:57,570 --> 00:01:00,570
Right. Congratulations
on winning the game today.

10
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:09,680
Hold on.

11
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,850
Your shoelace came undone.

12
00:01:15,620 --> 00:01:17,589
- I can get that.
- I'm done.

13
00:01:22,089 --> 00:01:23,330
I tied it twice,

14
00:01:25,430 --> 00:01:26,430
so it doesn't get loose.

15
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:37,480
I heard when your shoelace comes undone,

16
00:01:37,940 --> 00:01:40,210
it means you have met the one.

17
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:42,680
I tied it twice, so it doesn't get loose.

18
00:01:43,950 --> 00:01:44,950
I'm done.

19
00:01:55,390 --> 00:01:56,530
Get home safely.

20
00:01:57,730 --> 00:01:59,330
Okay. I will.

21
00:02:06,970 --> 00:02:09,670
(Go Woo-young)

22
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:20,480
(Go Woo-young)

23
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:35,800
=Episode 9,
Things You Notice Only After You Have Lost Them=

24
00:02:36,970 --> 00:02:38,970
(Do you want to become young again?)

25
00:02:39,070 --> 00:02:40,610
Hey, Da-jung.

26
00:02:41,810 --> 00:02:45,140
I'm glad that you got to
watch Si-woo's last game of his life.

27
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:46,640
What do you mean?

28
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,650
I thought the team advanced
to the next round.

29
00:02:48,950 --> 00:02:51,020
My team did advance to the next round,

30
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:54,450
but players like Si-woo will
only play these preliminary games.

31
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:58,120
Players who have shown me gratitude
ought to play in important games.

32
00:02:59,490 --> 00:03:00,560
How could you?

33
00:03:01,090 --> 00:03:03,590
Aren't you ashamed to face
your hardworking players?

34
00:03:03,690 --> 00:03:05,100
Gosh.

35
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:09,070
Anyway, before I decide on my lineup
for the next game,

36
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,500
I'm going to hold
one more parent-teacher conference.

37
00:03:11,570 --> 00:03:12,870
If this is your attitude,

38
00:03:12,940 --> 00:03:14,370
we have nothing to discuss.

39
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:15,640
If you change your mind,

40
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:17,640
call me.

41
00:03:27,890 --> 00:03:29,550
(Professor Yoon of K University)

42
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:31,590
(will be interrogated by the police)

43
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:34,129
(for the sexual assault charge
after last week's episode.)

44
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:35,560
("On the Site, 25 Hours")

45
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:38,560
(is waiting to hear from you.)

46
00:03:38,730 --> 00:03:41,500
Gi-tae, can "On the Site, 25 Hours"

47
00:03:41,570 --> 00:03:43,970
handle topics such as
bribery for college admission?

48
00:03:44,040 --> 00:03:46,170
Of course, as long as there are
witnesses and evidence,

49
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,470
we'd start right away.

50
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:51,210
(Anchorwoman Jung Da-jung)

51
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,160
- Boss!
- Hey!

52
00:04:12,230 --> 00:04:14,170
I told you not to call me that.

53
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:18,640
- I'm sorry.
- How many times do I have to tell you?

54
00:04:27,410 --> 00:04:28,750
Table for how many?

55
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:31,850
I'm here to see your boss.

56
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,080
Is he inside?

57
00:04:33,150 --> 00:04:34,150
Pardon?

58
00:04:35,290 --> 00:04:37,459
How do you know my boss?

59
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,620
I'm Il-kwon's friend.

60
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:43,830
I see. I don't think he's coming in today.

61
00:04:43,890 --> 00:04:45,030
Do you want me to call him?

62
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,030
No. I'll call him myself.

63
00:04:47,100 --> 00:04:48,100
Okay.

64
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:51,400
I checked, and I think it is Choi Il-kwon.

65
00:04:51,470 --> 00:04:52,500
I'll look into it some more.

66
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,900
Okay. Thank you.

67
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:00,980
Yes.

68
00:05:02,050 --> 00:05:04,180
Okay. I'll be there soon.

69
00:05:06,020 --> 00:05:07,020
Honey.

70
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:09,690
I'm going to step out for a bit.

71
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,820
- Are you just getting here, son?
- Yes.

72
00:05:12,890 --> 00:05:15,190
Oh, right. When was the main game again?

73
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:16,459
Don't get your hopes up.

74
00:05:16,530 --> 00:05:19,200
If the starting lineup changes, I might
not be able to play in the main game.

75
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:23,800
What?
Why would the starting lineup change?

76
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,870
I don't know.

77
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:33,640
Choi Il-kwon. Congratulations on
sending your kids to the finals.

78
00:05:33,709 --> 00:05:36,610
Gosh, high school finals isn't
something to congratulate me about.

79
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:39,620
I'm going to move up
to the college league next year,

80
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,120
so I'm not really that impressed.

81
00:05:41,190 --> 00:05:42,390
Oh, right.

82
00:05:42,650 --> 00:05:44,890
They decided on someone else
for that position.

83
00:05:48,690 --> 00:05:49,730
Wait.

84
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,460
What?

85
00:05:51,830 --> 00:05:54,530
We had no choice.

86
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,940
You're not upset, right?

87
00:06:01,210 --> 00:06:02,270
Why would I be?

88
00:06:02,340 --> 00:06:05,280
If a position at Hankuk University
opens up, I'll make you coach.

89
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:07,850
Just stay in the high school league
until then.

90
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,880
That's right. Okay?

91
00:06:11,150 --> 00:06:12,150
Okay.

92
00:06:14,590 --> 00:06:16,620
Oh, Mr. Bang. You're finally here.

93
00:06:16,690 --> 00:06:18,390
Right. Come over here.

94
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:21,990
They are the coaches at Hankuk University.

95
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:24,900
They're going to help Gi-yong a lot
when he goes to college,

96
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:26,660
so I thought it'd be nice
for you to meet them.

97
00:06:26,730 --> 00:06:28,800
Oh, I see. Hello.

98
00:06:28,870 --> 00:06:32,270
Hello. We heard a lot about Gi-yong.

99
00:06:32,340 --> 00:06:34,000
Right. Thank you.

100
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:37,810
- Please take good care of him.
- But

101
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:40,080
it's too late tonight.

102
00:06:40,140 --> 00:06:43,010
It's too bad, but let's make plans
to meet another time.

103
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:45,420
It's nice to meet you, Mr. Bang.

104
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:51,490
Mr. Bang.

105
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:55,790
We enjoyed our drinks today,
and you don't need to worry about Gi-yong.

106
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:56,990
Understand?

107
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:00,760
Thank you. Goodness.

108
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:12,980
Hey.

109
00:07:13,380 --> 00:07:15,880
Next time, be sure to secure me a spot.

110
00:07:15,950 --> 00:07:18,420
Of course.
We'll make sure of it for next time.

111
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,420
- Right.
- Do me the favor.

112
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,690
- We'll get going.
- I'm serious.

113
00:07:29,690 --> 00:07:31,760
My gosh.

114
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,870
What?

115
00:07:40,740 --> 00:07:43,310
(- It's me, Hong Dae-young.)
- Hello?

116
00:07:43,709 --> 00:07:44,710
What?

117
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:46,310
Hong Dae-young?

118
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,540
(Gosh.)

119
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:49,780
What brings you to call me?

120
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:50,950
Choi Il-kwon.

121
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,920
(I heard everything.)

122
00:07:59,160 --> 00:08:00,190
Really?

123
00:08:00,930 --> 00:08:01,930
So what?

124
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:04,930
Isn't making a living teaching basketball,
the sport you love, enough for you?

125
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:07,130
Why are you trying to make money
off of the kids?

126
00:08:07,530 --> 00:08:09,170
The sport I love?

127
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:10,800
Who?

128
00:08:11,140 --> 00:08:12,200
Me?

129
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:15,070
All throughout high school and college,
I gave tens of thousands to my coaches

130
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:16,839
for a chance to play a game,

131
00:08:16,910 --> 00:08:20,209
but I was always on edge worried
that I would get kicked out.

132
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:22,550
If you know that feeling,
that's more of a reason not to do this.

133
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:25,420
Why are you trying to live like them?

134
00:08:25,979 --> 00:08:29,150
Hey. Shouldn't I get to reap
as much as I sowed,

135
00:08:29,220 --> 00:08:30,290
(you jerk?)

136
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:33,560
Even though I lived my life getting money
to have kids play,

137
00:08:33,890 --> 00:08:35,790
don't you think
I'm living better than you?

138
00:08:36,130 --> 00:08:38,030
(How dare someone as foolish as you
try to lecture me?)

139
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,030
Goodbye!

140
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:43,570
Gosh, why are things like this today?

141
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,610
Are you Gi-yong's father?

142
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:57,750
Who are you?

143
00:08:57,820 --> 00:08:59,920
I'm Si-woo's mom. I called you before.

144
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:02,690
You said you were busy, so I came to you.

145
00:09:03,290 --> 00:09:06,760
We'll take care of our son,
so don't worry about us.

146
00:09:17,230 --> 00:09:20,840
(I want to gather the basketball team's parents
on Saturday night and talk,)

147
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:22,310
(can you come?)

148
00:09:22,370 --> 00:09:23,170
(Beef entrails, pork galbi, pork belly)

149
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:26,380
(I can go, but will everyone come?)

150
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,980
(Don't worry.)

151
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:30,850
(There's a way for everything.)

152
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:38,590
What are you guys doing with my phone?

153
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:41,290
Accomplice. You have to include
the world "accomplice".

154
00:09:42,630 --> 00:09:44,330
Next, "lawsuit".

155
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:46,130
"File a lawsuit".

156
00:09:48,570 --> 00:09:49,570
I sent it.

157
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:57,010
(I'm Go Deok-jin, father of Go Woo-young,
a member of the basketball team.)

158
00:09:57,070 --> 00:09:59,210
(I want to hold an emergency parent meeting...)

159
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,580
(regarding Coach Choi Il-kwon's corruption.)

160
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:04,010
(For your information,
if you choose not to attend this meeting,)

161
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,880
(I'll regard you as Coach Choi Il-kwon's accomplice)

162
00:10:05,950 --> 00:10:09,120
(and file a lawsuit against you with my personal lawyer.)

163
00:10:09,550 --> 00:10:13,520
(Then I will see you all
on Saturday night at 8 p.m. in the gymnasium.)

164
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:22,370
- I know.
- Seriously.

165
00:10:22,430 --> 00:10:25,100
(- I won't go. I refuse to go!)
- What's going on?

166
00:10:25,170 --> 00:10:27,300
Why should I go to the parent meeting?

167
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:29,370
I'm asking you for this favor.

168
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:31,440
In return, I'll clean the house,
do the laundry,

169
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:33,010
cook, and wash the dishes.

170
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,280
Those are all things that
you're supposed to do anyway.

171
00:10:35,350 --> 00:10:37,310
Right. Of course I should do that.

172
00:10:37,380 --> 00:10:38,650
Is he really a parent?

173
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,950
Is his son a maid?

174
00:10:40,020 --> 00:10:42,620
Then I'll give you more money
for my living expenses.

175
00:10:42,690 --> 00:10:43,650
Hey.

176
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:45,820
Has he been giving you money too?

177
00:10:45,890 --> 00:10:46,960
Of course.

178
00:10:47,190 --> 00:10:49,360
Should I let him live with me for free?
Am I a philanthropist?

179
00:10:49,430 --> 00:10:50,430
My gosh.

180
00:10:50,490 --> 00:10:52,430
He takes money from a high school student.

181
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,160
Regardless, I can't help you.

182
00:10:54,230 --> 00:10:55,330
Hey!

183
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,440
She's helping me, so why won't you?

184
00:10:58,570 --> 00:11:00,970
Honestly, she has no reason to help me.

185
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:03,140
But you have to help me.

186
00:11:03,210 --> 00:11:04,310
Why should I?

187
00:11:04,910 --> 00:11:06,680
You're my dad! Darn it!

188
00:11:06,740 --> 00:11:08,980
You punk. You only call me Dad
when you need something.

189
00:11:09,050 --> 00:11:11,220
Do you see me as a pushover, you jerk?

190
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:13,880
I asked to act like my dad,
so why are you cursing at me?

191
00:11:13,950 --> 00:11:16,920
That's what I'm saying. Why must I
act like your dad, you punk.

192
00:11:16,990 --> 00:11:19,820
Darn it. Have you ever acted
like a proper dad to me?

193
00:11:19,890 --> 00:11:20,960
I pay for living expenses.

194
00:11:21,020 --> 00:11:23,290
Really, you jerk?
Pay for the water bill then, you punk.

195
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,830
Pay for my property tax too, you jerk.

196
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:26,430
Gosh, darn it.
I don't have money for that.

197
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,000
Do you even know when to pay property tax?

198
00:11:28,070 --> 00:11:29,200
- What?
- It's around this time.

199
00:11:29,270 --> 00:11:31,940
Then put it under my name,
I'll pay for it then.

200
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,770
Both of them aren't normal.

201
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,910
(- Are you serious, you jerk?)
- That woman is strange too.

202
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:38,440
- Let's go. Hurry.
- Goodness.

203
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,480
I refuse to go.

204
00:11:42,850 --> 00:11:45,750
My gosh. I'm so busy,
why did he call us here?

205
00:11:45,820 --> 00:11:47,720
- What does he want?
- I don't have time for this.

206
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:50,350
- My gosh.
- Why would he ask us to come?

207
00:11:50,420 --> 00:11:52,390
What a waste of time.

208
00:11:52,460 --> 00:11:53,890
What is this?

209
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,830
What kind of punk is he?

210
00:11:55,890 --> 00:11:58,000
- Why did he call us here?
- Why would he ask us to come?

211
00:11:58,060 --> 00:12:01,400
Thank you for taking time from your busy
schedules to come here.

212
00:12:02,070 --> 00:12:03,500
I refuse to go!

213
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,570
I'm going to call Ms. Ok
to the meeting too.

214
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,540
- Ms. Ok?
- Yes.

215
00:12:10,610 --> 00:12:12,840
She thinks a lot about the students.

216
00:12:12,910 --> 00:12:15,880
But imagine what would happen
if you lead the parents

217
00:12:15,950 --> 00:12:17,080
to resolve this issue.

218
00:12:17,150 --> 00:12:18,850
She wouldn't be able to help
but fall in love.

219
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:21,050
Really?

220
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:28,930
Thank you for coming.

221
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,860
Of course I should be here.

222
00:12:35,070 --> 00:12:36,970
The reason I gathered all of you here

223
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:39,570
is so that we can get rid of
Coach Choi Il-kwon.

224
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:41,470
- That's enough.
- My gosh.

225
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:44,040
18 years ago, I was also a known member

226
00:12:44,110 --> 00:12:46,080
of Serim High School's basketball team.

227
00:12:46,740 --> 00:12:50,210
My son learned how to play basketball
from me, so he's a great player.

228
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:54,020
Really?

229
00:12:56,420 --> 00:12:57,450
Yes.

230
00:13:02,790 --> 00:13:04,460
To be honest, there was a coach

231
00:13:04,530 --> 00:13:06,430
who asked for money 18 years ago too.

232
00:13:06,830 --> 00:13:09,570
However, my parents didn't give him money.

233
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:11,100
Why?

234
00:13:11,340 --> 00:13:13,170
Because they believed in me.

235
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,940
That's the reason why I can stand here
without shame

236
00:13:16,010 --> 00:13:17,710
in front of all of you today.

237
00:13:17,770 --> 00:13:18,780
Excuse me.

238
00:13:19,380 --> 00:13:22,080
What does that have to do
with Coach Choi Il-kwon?

239
00:13:22,150 --> 00:13:25,680
My fellow alumnus, Choi Il-kwon,
wasn't always such a bad guy.

240
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:26,850
But

241
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:30,290
do you know when he started
acting this way?

242
00:13:30,850 --> 00:13:33,920
(Choi Il-kwon)

243
00:13:34,420 --> 00:13:35,830
Did you get it ready?

244
00:13:35,830 --> 00:13:36,890
(Serim High School)

245
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:42,330
There won't be a problem with the starting lineup, right?

246
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,500
Of course not.

247
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:49,210
(Choi Il-kwon)

248
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,520
Go Deok-jin, listen carefully.

249
00:13:59,580 --> 00:14:01,820
If you tell anyone about what you saw,
I won't leave you alone.

250
00:14:01,890 --> 00:14:04,690
Okay. I won't tell anyone that your dad
gave the coach money.

251
00:14:04,760 --> 00:14:06,160
Shut your mouth!

252
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,600
(After that day, Choi Il-kwon)

253
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:15,230
took money from me,

254
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:17,470
and he started hitting me.

255
00:14:17,830 --> 00:14:20,200
I thought he came to his senses
when he became a teacher,

256
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:22,270
but he's still taking money from people.

257
00:14:22,370 --> 00:14:24,310
Just like what that coach did 18 years ago

258
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:26,340
to Choi Il-kwon's father.

