00:45:26,410 --> 00:45:28,450
What? Sir?

802
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:34,190
What's with that reaction?

803
00:45:40,630 --> 00:45:42,830
Don't act like you know this
in front of the other kids.

804
00:45:43,290 --> 00:45:44,460
Just stay quiet.

805
00:45:59,980 --> 00:46:01,780
(I can never stay quiet!)

806
00:46:01,850 --> 00:46:03,510
(I'll protect my daughter.)

807
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,280
Goodnight.

808
00:46:11,460 --> 00:46:12,890
Do you have something to say?

809
00:46:13,990 --> 00:46:16,360
- Yes.
- What is it?

810
00:46:21,230 --> 00:46:23,230
I actually...

811
00:46:24,700 --> 00:46:26,040
Hello.

812
00:46:27,910 --> 00:46:28,910
What?

813
00:46:31,240 --> 00:46:33,880
- Why are you here?
- Why would I be at a convenience store?

814
00:46:45,790 --> 00:46:47,490
I hear that the basketball team has
a new coach.

815
00:46:48,260 --> 00:46:49,790
How is he?

816
00:46:51,530 --> 00:46:53,530
He's good.

817
00:46:54,700 --> 00:46:56,400
Did you just worry about me?

818
00:46:57,600 --> 00:47:00,870
Worry? No. I'm just curious.

819
00:47:03,810 --> 00:47:04,910
Here.

820
00:47:07,450 --> 00:47:08,650
You can drink this one.

821
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:12,150
Why are you giving this to me?

822
00:47:12,220 --> 00:47:13,680
It's buy 1 get 1 free.

823
00:47:14,220 --> 00:47:16,120
I just want one,
and I can't throw the other away.

824
00:47:23,930 --> 00:47:25,060
Seo Ji-ho!

825
00:47:27,470 --> 00:47:29,700
What? I thought you were
getting rid of it.

826
00:47:37,580 --> 00:47:39,110
Why are you two here?

827
00:47:49,390 --> 00:47:50,660
Aren't you two going to go home?

828
00:47:54,290 --> 00:47:55,660
You're not going, either.

829
00:47:55,730 --> 00:47:58,360
I'm waiting to walk Si-a home.

830
00:47:58,430 --> 00:47:59,430
Why would you do that?

831
00:47:59,860 --> 00:48:00,870
"Why"?

832
00:48:00,930 --> 00:48:03,400
Because it's a scary world out there.

833
00:48:03,470 --> 00:48:06,600
(- I'm leaving now!
- Good work. Get home safely.)

834
00:48:06,670 --> 00:48:08,770
(Thank you. Goodnight.)

835
00:48:11,680 --> 00:48:13,980
- Si-a, let's go.
- Sure.

836
00:48:14,980 --> 00:48:16,380
Why are you all still here?

837
00:48:16,450 --> 00:48:18,620
Your father asked me to do something.

838
00:48:18,680 --> 00:48:20,590
What did he ask you to do?

839
00:48:20,650 --> 00:48:22,190
I'll tell you as we walk.

840
00:48:24,020 --> 00:48:26,090
Get home safely, you two.

841
00:48:27,990 --> 00:48:29,060
Let's go.

842
00:48:31,630 --> 00:48:32,730
What are you doing? Come on.

843
00:48:33,430 --> 00:48:34,500
All right.

844
00:48:36,870 --> 00:48:37,940
Bye.

845
00:48:43,040 --> 00:48:44,640
- That punk!
- That punk!

846
00:48:46,710 --> 00:48:47,750
Come on.

847
00:48:51,950 --> 00:48:53,050
What do you

848
00:48:53,890 --> 00:48:55,350
think of those two?

849
00:48:56,050 --> 00:48:57,120
Those two?

850
00:48:58,620 --> 00:49:00,260
Seo Ji-ho and Gu Ja-sung.

851
00:49:00,760 --> 00:49:02,860
Not as friends, but as men.

852
00:49:03,590 --> 00:49:05,000
Are you insane?

853
00:49:05,330 --> 00:49:07,230
I've been friends with Ji-ho for ten years!

854
00:49:07,300 --> 00:49:09,030
How can I see him as a man?

855
00:49:10,370 --> 00:49:12,240
And I get furious

856
00:49:12,300 --> 00:49:14,910
just thinking about
how Ja-sung bullied Si-woo.

857
00:49:15,170 --> 00:49:16,840
Goodness, he's annoying.

858
00:49:23,180 --> 00:49:24,250
Wait.

859
00:49:25,480 --> 00:49:27,080
Why are you going the dark way?

860
00:49:27,750 --> 00:49:28,890
This is the faster way.

861
00:49:31,320 --> 00:49:33,690
There's not a lot of people around,
and it's dark.

862
00:49:34,260 --> 00:49:35,490
There are no surveillance cameras, either.

863
00:49:35,560 --> 00:49:37,130
Go through a brighter area.

864
00:49:37,190 --> 00:49:39,160
It's already dangerous for you
to be out so late.

865
00:49:39,230 --> 00:49:41,170
Stop nagging.

866
00:49:41,470 --> 00:49:43,370
- Am I a kid?
- Yes, you are.

867
00:49:43,430 --> 00:49:44,570
And

868
00:49:46,440 --> 00:49:47,670
take this around with you.

869
00:49:47,910 --> 00:49:49,540
It's an alarm in case of danger.

870
00:49:51,810 --> 00:49:53,440
You can use it.

871
00:49:53,510 --> 00:49:56,110
Your father asked me to give it to you.
Take it.

872
00:49:57,720 --> 00:49:58,850
Goodness.

873
00:50:09,330 --> 00:50:10,390
Si-a!

874
00:50:11,160 --> 00:50:12,230
Mom!

875
00:50:14,430 --> 00:50:15,830
You two are coming together?

876
00:50:16,270 --> 00:50:18,970
No, he just walked me home.

877
00:50:21,810 --> 00:50:22,910
You're coming home quite late.

878
00:50:23,010 --> 00:50:25,040
Yes, work ended late.

879
00:50:25,110 --> 00:50:27,610
It's late. You should get home quickly.

880
00:50:27,680 --> 00:50:28,680
Yes, ma'am.

881
00:50:29,550 --> 00:50:31,650
- Get home safely.
- All right.

882
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:32,920
Let's go.

883
00:50:33,480 --> 00:50:34,550
Bye.

884
00:50:37,590 --> 00:50:39,120
Did I interrupt you two?

885
00:50:39,390 --> 00:50:41,230
What are you talking about?

886
00:50:41,460 --> 00:50:43,390
He and I are nothing like that.

887
00:50:43,530 --> 00:50:45,800
It's more suspicious
that you're getting so mad.

888
00:50:46,460 --> 00:50:48,230
I'm telling you!

889
00:50:48,700 --> 00:50:51,440
Gosh, I mean it!

890
00:51:25,740 --> 00:51:26,670
(Observation report 25)

891
00:51:26,670 --> 00:51:28,340
(10:10 p.m.)

892
00:51:28,510 --> 00:51:29,940
(Met up with his family.)

893
00:51:30,110 --> 00:51:32,480
(10:30 p.m.)

894
00:51:32,640 --> 00:51:34,710
(Hasn't left the house since coming back.)

895
00:51:35,550 --> 00:51:37,720
(Observation complete.)

896
00:51:37,780 --> 00:51:38,820
(Carrying out)

897
00:51:40,020 --> 00:51:41,390
(the plan tomorrow.)

898
00:51:41,390 --> 00:51:43,120
(Content)

899
00:51:54,100 --> 00:51:56,800
Hey, can we talk for a moment?

900
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:08,080
What's wrong?

901
00:52:11,180 --> 00:52:12,780
Don't be too shocked.

902
00:52:12,950 --> 00:52:14,650
I heard from Producer Park,

903
00:52:14,720 --> 00:52:17,760
but apparently, only three of us will be
signing full contracts.

904
00:52:18,860 --> 00:52:21,390
What about the other one?

905
00:52:22,190 --> 00:52:23,690
They're going to get fired.

906
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:27,430
You all didn't know about this, right?

907
00:52:27,570 --> 00:52:28,770
I had no idea.

908
00:52:28,900 --> 00:52:29,900
Same here.

909
00:52:31,370 --> 00:52:32,370
Me neither.

910
00:52:32,570 --> 00:52:34,970
Shouldn't we do something about it?

911
00:52:37,370 --> 00:52:39,540
Let's check with HR first.

912
00:52:39,610 --> 00:52:42,250
And if it is true, why don't we tell them

913
00:52:42,310 --> 00:52:45,750
as a group that
the decision they made isn't fair?

914
00:52:48,220 --> 00:52:50,520
The company already made a decision.

915
00:52:50,620 --> 00:52:53,020
Do you think by taking action,
we'll be able to change anything?

916
00:52:53,190 --> 00:52:55,560
Then, do you just want to sit back
and do nothing?

917
00:52:55,630 --> 00:52:57,290
This is the reality we are in.

918
00:52:57,360 --> 00:52:59,330
We must do our best to survive here.

919
00:53:01,230 --> 00:53:04,940
Ms. Kwon, if we don't have
a united front, this is useless.

920
00:53:05,870 --> 00:53:08,310
I think you're letting your emotions
make decisions for you right now.

921
00:53:08,370 --> 00:53:10,240
Why don't you be rational?

922
00:53:10,310 --> 00:53:13,340
And if you want to bring this up,
count me out.

923
00:53:13,410 --> 00:53:15,080
Then, I'll get going.

924
00:53:15,080 --> 00:53:16,050
(Conference Room)

925
00:53:20,120 --> 00:53:22,520
Oh, my. She's so cold.

926
00:53:23,090 --> 00:53:24,920
So she sees us as competition, right?

927
00:53:25,290 --> 00:53:27,560
What programs are you on?
I have a current affairs program.

928
00:53:27,630 --> 00:53:29,560
Ja-young is on a culture program
and a radio show.

929
00:53:29,630 --> 00:53:31,100
That... Yu-mi has

930
00:53:32,460 --> 00:53:35,070
variety shows and baseball interviews.
And you, Da-jung...

931
00:53:37,600 --> 00:53:40,240
Only I don't have a fixed program.

932
00:53:43,570 --> 00:53:46,440
I'm sure you'll get offers
to be on another show soon.

933
00:53:46,980 --> 00:53:48,080
Right.

934
00:53:48,380 --> 00:53:49,750
Don't worry.

935
00:53:59,860 --> 00:54:00,960
Hello.

936
00:54:01,930 --> 00:54:03,460
You're Ms. Jung Da-jung, right?

937
00:54:04,400 --> 00:54:05,960
I'm Park Gi-seong,
a variety show producer.

938
00:54:06,030 --> 00:54:07,830
This is Lee Bo-ra, a variety show writer.

939
00:54:08,970 --> 00:54:10,170
Hello.

940
00:54:10,430 --> 00:54:13,000
- The producer came in person.
- Right.

941
00:54:13,100 --> 00:54:14,810
It's a pilot program for the holiday.

942
00:54:14,870 --> 00:54:17,240
And we really want to hire you as the MC.

943
00:54:17,370 --> 00:54:19,610
If this does well,
this might become a regular show.

944
00:54:20,540 --> 00:54:21,580
MC?

945
00:54:22,310 --> 00:54:23,380
Awesome!

946
00:54:24,380 --> 00:54:27,150
But why are you offering me that job?

947
00:54:27,820 --> 00:54:29,520
(Program Proposal for "Couples in Crises")

948
00:54:30,090 --> 00:54:31,390
This show is about divorce.

949
00:54:31,460 --> 00:54:33,760
We really want you to host the show.

950
00:54:34,360 --> 00:54:35,390
I see.

951
00:54:43,370 --> 00:54:45,600
This is the data we have
from last year's events.

952
00:54:45,670 --> 00:54:47,610
There are some overlapping parts
with this year.

953
00:54:47,670 --> 00:54:50,740
I have someone bringing me
this year's version from my house.

954
00:54:53,440 --> 00:54:55,780
I hope you're not trying
to stall time like last time.

955
00:54:55,880 --> 00:54:57,750
To wait for your son who's my fan.

956
00:54:58,320 --> 00:55:00,580
He's not your fan anymore.

957
00:55:00,650 --> 00:55:01,890
Actually, he hates you now.

958
00:55:02,790 --> 00:55:03,850
That's odd.

959
00:55:04,260 --> 00:55:06,120
I'm performing better these days.

960
00:55:06,190 --> 00:55:09,190
I guess he's even more jealous
because you're performing better now.

961
00:55:09,260 --> 00:55:11,700
As a matter of fact, you're better
than him in so many ways.

962
00:55:12,160 --> 00:55:14,470
Pardon? What do you mean?

963
00:55:15,330 --> 00:55:17,070
Am I your errand boy now?

964
00:55:21,370 --> 00:55:22,370
Wait.

965
00:55:26,510 --> 00:55:28,150
You were his son?

966
00:55:29,410 --> 00:55:30,610
Hey, nice to see you.

967
00:55:32,850 --> 00:55:34,180
You needed this, right?

968
00:55:34,490 --> 00:55:36,850
Right. That's the one.
Wait for me outside.

969
00:55:45,400 --> 00:55:46,760
He must really hate me.

970
00:55:46,830 --> 00:55:48,030
I told you so.

971
00:55:48,230 --> 00:55:49,930
Anyway, you have the new files.

972
00:55:50,000 --> 00:55:51,840
Let's go over them
and talk business first.

973
00:55:52,270 --> 00:55:53,270
Sure.

974
00:56:22,130 --> 00:56:25,270
They've gone mad. They want you
to host a show about divorce?

975
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:28,510
If I don't take this show,

976
00:56:28,640 --> 00:56:30,040
I might get fired.

977
00:56:30,270 --> 00:56:31,280
What?

978
00:56:31,580 --> 00:56:32,780
Why?

979
00:56:33,610 --> 00:56:36,480
They'll only hire three people
after the probationary period.

980
00:56:37,210 --> 00:56:39,250
And I'm the only one without a show.

981
00:56:40,750 --> 00:56:44,250
Ae-rin, if I do take this show,

982
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:45,560
can you help me?

983
00:56:47,260 --> 00:56:48,290
I'm livid,

984
00:56:48,360 --> 00:56:50,490
so let's eat something spicy
that burns our stomachs.

985
00:56:51,660 --> 00:56:54,260
No. I don't have an appetite.

986
00:56:54,600 --> 00:56:56,170
Don't be like that. Come with me.

987
00:56:56,230 --> 00:56:58,940
You always ate spicy food
when you were stressed out.

988
00:56:59,500 --> 00:57:00,500
Next time.

989
00:57:02,310 --> 00:57:05,610
I can tell from your face that
you haven't eaten a single meal today.

990
00:57:17,120 --> 00:57:18,120
Ms. Jung.

991
00:57:19,020 --> 00:57:21,560
What? Mr. Ye.

992
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:24,260
Gosh, this area must have good chill.

993
00:57:24,460 --> 00:57:26,060
I run into you whenever I'm here.

994
00:57:26,600 --> 00:57:30,330
Well, are you here because of work?

995
00:57:30,800 --> 00:57:32,840
Yes. I am. Because of you.

996
00:57:33,570 --> 00:57:35,270
- Pardon?
- I came here because of you,

997
00:57:35,570 --> 00:57:37,010
so I can see you.

998
00:57:38,610 --> 00:57:40,140
I mean it.

999
00:57:41,310 --> 00:57:42,310
Look.

1000
00:57:45,080 --> 00:57:47,720
- What?
- I was leaving after a business meeting.

1001
00:57:47,790 --> 00:57:50,150
And I saw you walking
on the street, passing by.

1002
00:57:51,620 --> 00:57:53,560
If you haven't had dinner,
can you join me?

1003
00:57:54,460 --> 00:57:58,300
Well, I had a late lunch.

1004
00:57:59,200 --> 00:58:01,000
Then, can you sit in front of me?

1005
00:58:01,300 --> 00:58:02,870
I can't eat at restaurants by myself.

1006
00:58:04,500 --> 00:58:07,040
Gosh. I'm starving. Goodness.

1007
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:09,740
I'm out of energy too.

1008
00:58:16,710 --> 00:58:19,620
The chef here serves amazing food.

1009
00:58:21,190 --> 00:58:23,520
Her spicy stir-fried pork is to die for.

1010
00:58:24,860 --> 00:58:27,460
- Ma'am.
- Look at you, Ji-hoon.

1011
00:58:27,520 --> 00:58:29,790
Where have you been all this time?
You're making me sad.

1012
00:58:29,860 --> 00:58:32,400
I'm sorry. It's the baseball season.
I've been busy.

1013
00:58:35,500 --> 00:58:36,500
What?

1014
00:58:37,840 --> 00:58:39,040
Aren't you Ms. Jung Da-jung?

1015
00:58:39,740 --> 00:58:41,570
Do you know me?

1016
00:58:41,640 --> 00:58:45,940
Of course! I'm a huge fan of yours.

1017
00:58:46,540 --> 00:58:49,180
By the way,
what's going on between you two?

1018
00:58:49,280 --> 00:58:51,220
You've never brought a lady here.

1019
00:58:51,280 --> 00:58:52,750
She's a close colleague.

1020
00:58:52,820 --> 00:58:54,650
Don't get the wrong idea.
Spicy pork, please.

1021
00:58:55,290 --> 00:58:56,320
Sure.

1022
00:58:57,890 --> 00:59:00,490
Oh, right. Ma'am,
put a lot of chili pepper powder!

1023
00:59:00,560 --> 00:59:02,160
Make it spicy that it burns our stomachs!

1024
00:59:02,860 --> 00:59:04,430
A lot of chili pepper powder?

1025
00:59:04,500 --> 00:59:06,530
He can't even handle spicy food.

1026
00:59:09,500 --> 00:59:10,670
Whatever.

1027
00:59:10,870 --> 00:59:13,970
All right. Let's do this, then.

1028
00:59:32,820 --> 00:59:34,160
My gosh, it's so good.

1029
00:59:34,630 --> 00:59:36,260
My stress is gone now!

1030
00:59:36,930 --> 00:59:37,930
Oh, right.

1031
00:59:39,460 --> 00:59:40,560
You should try it.

1032
00:59:41,330 --> 00:59:42,900
No. I'm good.

1033
00:59:42,970 --> 00:59:45,500
It's really good.
Just have one bite. Please?

1034
00:59:47,870 --> 00:59:48,870
All right, then.

1035
00:59:55,350 --> 00:59:58,150
My gosh, it's so good.

1036
00:59:58,350 --> 01:00:00,280
Right? Eat with me.

1037
01:00:01,020 --> 01:00:03,520
Ma'am, one more bowl of rice!

1038
01:00:15,800 --> 01:00:17,400
Ms. Jung!

1039
01:00:21,570 --> 01:00:23,270
Can you give me an autograph?

1040
01:00:23,740 --> 01:00:24,740
An autograph?

1041
01:00:24,810 --> 01:00:27,380
A celebrity came to my restaurant.
I should hang it up.

1042
01:00:28,310 --> 01:00:29,310
(Ma'am!)

1043
01:00:30,110 --> 01:00:31,620
I'm coming!

1044
01:00:32,520 --> 01:00:34,850
Can you sign it and put it on the counter?

1045
01:00:36,490 --> 01:00:38,520
You look much prettier in person.

1046
01:00:42,730 --> 01:00:43,760
This feels weird.

1047
01:00:44,160 --> 01:00:46,830
I've only signed contracts up until now.

1048
01:00:49,130 --> 01:00:50,200
Hold on.

1049
01:00:50,930 --> 01:00:52,400
Don't sign it yet.

1050
01:01:05,020 --> 01:01:07,780
Here.
This is the glove I wear for my games.

1051
01:01:08,720 --> 01:01:11,050
- And?
- Sign my glove first.

1052
01:01:11,120 --> 01:01:12,320
I'm your number one fan, remember?

1053
01:01:15,090 --> 01:01:16,990
- What?
- Come on. Please.

1054
01:01:17,330 --> 01:01:18,930
This is really important to me.

1055
01:01:24,600 --> 01:01:25,670
Okay.

1056
01:01:33,710 --> 01:01:34,710
Thank you.

1057
01:01:43,020 --> 01:01:45,360
Gosh, it burns. It's killing me.

1058
01:01:59,640 --> 01:02:02,410
(I'll always root for you.
From Jung Da-jung.)

1059
01:02:10,710 --> 01:02:12,620
- She lost all of her shows?
- Yes.

1060
01:02:12,950 --> 01:02:16,420
But she got an offer to host
a show about divorce.

1061
01:02:16,950 --> 01:02:18,420
What does she want to do?

1062
01:02:19,960 --> 01:02:21,690
She thinks it's her last chance.

1063
01:02:25,730 --> 01:02:27,000
Then, she should take it.

1064
01:02:27,600 --> 01:02:28,630
What?

1065
01:02:30,470 --> 01:02:32,440
If the show airs, people will talk.

1066
01:02:32,500 --> 01:02:34,470
We don't even know how people will react.

1067
01:02:34,570 --> 01:02:37,410
This might take a toll on Da-jung
and your kids.

1068
01:02:37,470 --> 01:02:39,140
I'm sure she's aware of it.

1069
01:02:40,680 --> 01:02:43,080
But if she thinks this is her last chance

1070
01:02:45,250 --> 01:02:46,780
and if she must do it,

1071
01:02:47,880 --> 01:02:48,990
I don't think

1072
01:02:52,460 --> 01:02:54,930
she's making this decision
just for herself.

1073
01:03:15,180 --> 01:03:17,010
- My gosh.
- Gosh.

1074
01:03:17,550 --> 01:03:20,420
- This is beautiful.
- Awesome.

1075
01:03:20,580 --> 01:03:22,190
It's so pretty.

1076
01:03:22,920 --> 01:03:24,190
Gosh.

1077
01:03:24,250 --> 01:03:25,960
- This is amazing.
- Kids grow up so fast.

1078
01:03:26,020 --> 01:03:27,860
I want them to slow down a bit.

1079
01:03:27,920 --> 01:03:31,030
Right. It's sad to see them
grow up so quickly.

1080
01:03:31,460 --> 01:03:34,800
Once they all grow up, they won't
join us for the fireworks, right?

1081
01:03:34,870 --> 01:03:37,400
That's all right. We have each other.

1082
01:03:39,570 --> 01:03:40,670
Dae-young.

1083
01:03:41,970 --> 01:03:43,410
Actually,

1084
01:03:44,040 --> 01:03:46,480
I got the result from the interview
for the anchorwoman position.

1085
01:03:47,180 --> 01:03:49,410
Really? Did you get it?

1086
01:03:50,410 --> 01:03:51,620
I didn't get it.

1087
01:03:52,820 --> 01:03:54,790
Why would you say that with a smile on?

1088
01:03:56,150 --> 01:03:57,520
I was happy.

1089
01:03:57,690 --> 01:03:59,790
When I went for the interview,

1090
01:04:00,590 --> 01:04:03,090
the fact that I was at a TV station

1091
01:04:03,790 --> 01:04:05,060
made me so happy.

1092
01:04:06,260 --> 01:04:08,970
So I'm going to give it my all.

1093
01:04:09,470 --> 01:04:12,040
I want to show our kids how I'll keep

1094
01:04:12,100 --> 01:04:14,840
trying and challenging myself.

1095
01:04:15,540 --> 01:04:16,910
And I'll make my dream come true

1096
01:04:17,610 --> 01:04:20,510
and make them proud as a cool mother.

1097
01:04:22,810 --> 01:04:25,680
Yes. I'm sure you can do it.

1098
01:04:30,350 --> 01:04:32,860
- Come here.
- My goodness. Look!

1099
01:04:32,920 --> 01:04:35,060
- That one too.
- That's pretty too.

1100
01:04:56,880 --> 01:04:58,720
(Are you all coming home late tonight?)

1101
01:04:58,780 --> 01:05:01,080
(Group Chatroom, 4)

1102
01:05:01,150 --> 01:05:03,120
(I have plans. I'll be late.)

1103
01:05:04,050 --> 01:05:06,190
(I'm going to practice basketball
before I go home.)

1104
01:05:07,420 --> 01:05:09,290
(I'm coming home late today.)

1105
01:05:14,330 --> 01:05:16,030
I don't want to watch it alone.

1106
01:05:25,280 --> 01:05:26,340
What?

1107
01:05:27,640 --> 01:05:29,380
I have something to give you.

1108
01:05:38,660 --> 01:05:40,860
Gosh, I didn't know
these photos still existed.

1109
01:05:41,120 --> 01:05:43,360
I was preparing for the festival.
I thought they were cool.

1110
01:05:44,390 --> 01:05:45,460
By the way,

1111
01:05:45,930 --> 01:05:47,860
how did you know this was me
in the photos?

1112
01:05:47,930 --> 01:05:49,400
I changed a lot.

1113
01:05:49,470 --> 01:05:51,230
Gosh, you didn't.

1114
01:05:51,740 --> 01:05:53,170
You're still pretty.

1115
01:05:53,940 --> 01:05:54,940
What?

1116
01:05:57,510 --> 01:06:00,680
Si-a is the spitting image of you.

1117
01:06:01,680 --> 01:06:04,150
Oh, right. Do you want to see her photos?

1118
01:06:10,990 --> 01:06:12,220
She's cute.

1119
01:06:18,090 --> 01:06:19,900
Is that Si-woo?

1120
01:06:19,960 --> 01:06:20,960
Isn't he amazing?

1121
01:06:21,030 --> 01:06:23,870
His eyes change
whenever he plays basketball.

1122
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:28,510
I should have gone
to his games more often.

1123
01:06:29,270 --> 01:06:30,340
What a shame.

1124
01:06:33,010 --> 01:06:34,740
You've been busy with work.

1125
01:06:35,350 --> 01:06:37,180
You raised them as a working mom.

1126
01:06:37,580 --> 01:06:38,950
You're incredible.

1127
01:06:41,280 --> 01:06:42,450
Why do you

1128
01:06:43,090 --> 01:06:44,620
talk like a grown-up?

1129
01:06:44,690 --> 01:06:46,820
I might not look old,
but I'm very old on the inside.

1130
01:06:49,090 --> 01:06:51,630
I still get nervous of making mistakes

1131
01:06:51,700 --> 01:06:53,200
before my games.

1132
01:06:54,330 --> 01:06:55,470
But

1133
01:06:57,170 --> 01:06:58,400
when I see you on TV,

1134
01:06:59,170 --> 01:07:01,300
you don't seem nervous at all.

1135
01:07:02,170 --> 01:07:03,940
And you never make mistakes.

1136
01:07:06,140 --> 01:07:07,640
Whenever I see you on TV,

1137
01:07:08,080 --> 01:07:09,710
I always think you're so cool.

1138
01:07:11,110 --> 01:07:13,380
Gosh. No, I'm not.

1139
01:07:13,450 --> 01:07:14,650
I mean it.

1140
01:07:14,950 --> 01:07:17,390
Si-a and Si-woo are rooting for you too.

1141
01:07:17,890 --> 01:07:19,720
- Really?
- Yes.

1142
01:07:19,890 --> 01:07:23,230
So you should continue showing them
how great you are on TV.

1143
01:07:25,200 --> 01:07:26,260
Thank you.

1144
01:07:39,380 --> 01:07:40,410
It started.

1145
01:07:52,220 --> 01:07:53,260
(Da-jung,)

1146
01:07:56,460 --> 01:07:57,520
(you are)

1147
01:07:58,260 --> 01:07:59,760
(doing a great job.)

1148
01:08:00,560 --> 01:08:03,270
(So don't worry.)

1149
01:08:09,340 --> 01:08:10,400
(I'm sure)

1150
01:08:11,570 --> 01:08:12,880
(you'll do a great job again.)

1151
01:08:24,020 --> 01:08:25,220
How beautiful.

1152
01:08:38,270 --> 01:08:40,540
(There are some things you notice
only after you have lost them.)

1153
01:08:43,230 --> 01:08:46,180
Thank you for today. Get home safely.

1154
01:08:50,210 --> 01:08:52,250
(A smile of my loved one.)

1155
01:08:54,250 --> 01:08:55,750
(All right. Raise your left hand!)

1156
01:08:55,820 --> 01:08:58,760
(Time you spent with your family.)

1157
01:09:02,860 --> 01:09:04,130
(When I had them,)

1158
01:09:05,820 --> 01:09:07,460
(I didn't know)

1159
01:09:08,060 --> 01:09:09,500
(how precious)

1160
01:09:10,630 --> 01:09:12,170
(they had been.)

1161
01:09:26,980 --> 01:09:28,180
Yu-ju!

1162
01:09:30,190 --> 01:09:31,390
Mom!

1163
01:09:38,660 --> 01:09:38,930
No, Yu-ju!

1164
01:09:38,930 --> 01:09:40,000
(Van Parcel Service)
No, Yu-ju!

1165
01:09:40,000 --> 01:09:40,400
No, Yu-ju!

1166
01:09:40,760 --> 01:09:42,670
Yu-ju!

1167
01:09:58,580 --> 01:10:00,750
All right. Transport him to the OR slowly.

1168
01:10:06,690 --> 01:10:09,660
He was in a car accident. His name is
Hong Dae-young. He was born in 1983.

1169
01:10:25,210 --> 01:10:28,040
(8 years ago)

1170
01:10:32,380 --> 01:10:34,320
Dae-young. Hong Dae-young!

1171
01:10:35,450 --> 01:10:38,120
- Dae-young!
- Hold on.

1172
01:10:38,820 --> 01:10:40,190
Dae-young.

1173
01:10:40,590 --> 01:10:42,560
Your mom is calling you.

1174
01:10:43,990 --> 01:10:45,090
Okay!

1175
01:10:53,270 --> 01:10:55,370
Let the kids play a bit more. Okay?

1176
01:10:55,840 --> 01:10:57,140
They are having fun.

1177
01:10:57,310 --> 01:10:59,610
Kids' cafes are so convenient.

1178
01:10:59,910 --> 01:11:01,710
But why now,
when our kids are all grown up?

1179
01:11:01,980 --> 01:11:03,050
Right.

1180
01:11:03,110 --> 01:11:04,710
Do you want to play with me?

1181
01:11:05,380 --> 01:11:06,380
Sure.

1182
01:11:11,750 --> 01:11:13,360
Who is that guy?
Why is he holding her hand?

1183
01:11:13,420 --> 01:11:15,020
He must be Si-a's friend.

1184
01:11:16,330 --> 01:11:17,430
Ja-sung.

1185
01:11:17,490 --> 01:11:20,100
"Ja-sung"? I don't think he's her friend.

1186
01:11:21,360 --> 01:11:24,030
I bet when Si-a brings
her future husband home,

1187
01:11:24,100 --> 01:11:25,700
you're going to throw a fit.

1188
01:11:26,470 --> 01:11:28,370
- What?
- Isn't it obvious?

1189
01:11:28,440 --> 01:11:31,240
She's going to date
and have boyfriends later.

1190
01:11:31,310 --> 01:11:32,810
And she'll get married too.

1191
01:11:33,780 --> 01:11:36,210
What will you do
when she brings her boyfriend home?

1192
01:11:36,910 --> 01:11:39,420
First, I'm going to break his leg.

1193
01:11:39,480 --> 01:11:40,750
- What?
- And then,

1194
01:11:40,820 --> 01:11:42,450
if he's a nice man, I'll fix his leg.

1195
01:11:43,090 --> 01:11:45,360
And if he's a bad man, I'll break his other leg.

1196
01:11:45,420 --> 01:11:46,490
Goodness.

1197
01:11:47,390 --> 01:11:49,690
I don't think Si-a will be able to get married in this life.

1198
01:11:49,760 --> 01:11:51,490
Don't bring up stuff like that.

1199
01:11:53,160 --> 01:11:55,060
I'm already tearing up.

1200
01:11:56,300 --> 01:11:58,970
It looks like I'm raising 3 kids, not 2.

1201
01:12:00,970 --> 01:12:04,510
Come here, my baby. My poor baby.

1202
01:12:04,840 --> 01:12:06,980
Were you sad? Is that it?

